column2: Have been away for 5 weeks or we would have reported sooner.  Last year mid-summer readings were 23'.
Last year readings were 23! what is going on
Hazy day. lake level lower this year.
Lake level is falling.  Lowest we've ever seen it in 15 years.
Water level extremely high. Lots of rain this year. Lake is not as clear as last summer.

Lake is even higher than last summer.  Some Piers are flooded. The loon pair abandon their eggs on the floating nest and restarted on the western shore. 1 baby loon hatched.  There is a fox den with 5 kits on the south shore.  Otters were spotted but have now left.
Maximum depth was 53 feet measured with a depth finder
